[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":434},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2019\u002F09\u002F24\u002Fcustomize-windows-terminal-with-oh-my-posh\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2019\u002F09\u002F24\u002Fcustomize-windows-terminal-with-oh-my-posh\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2019\u002F09\u002F24\u002Fcustomize-windows-terminal-with-oh-my-posh\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2019\u002F09\u002F24\u002Fcustomize-windows-terminal-with-oh-my-posh\u002F":409,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2019\u002F09\u002F24\u002Fcustomize-windows-terminal-with-oh-my-posh\u002F":418},"\u002Fother\u002F20190924\u002F3446878284\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":391,"date":392,"description":393,"extension":394,"lang":395,"meta":396,"navigation":397,"path":398,"readingMinutes":399,"seo":400,"standalone":401,"stem":402,"tags":403,"tldr":406,"updated":406,"url":407,"__hash__":408},"content\u002Fen\u002FMisc\u002Fcustomize-windows-terminal-with-oh-my-posh.md","Customize Windows Terminal with oh-my-posh (PowerShell Prompt + Windows Terminal Setup)","8788428343",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":375},"minimark",[11,16,20,30,34,37,44,47,50,55,63,70,76,80,83,89,92,98,105,114,118,122,125,141,148,152,161,167,171,177,183,186,197,204,226,229,242,246,249,254,257,268,271,275,283,289,292,298,302,305,311,318,323,326,332,335,341,344,362,365,371],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"If you spend most of your day in a terminal, staring at the same plain prompt gets boring fast. This post walks through making Windows PowerShell pretty.",[21,22,23],"blockquote",{},[17,24,25,29],{},[26,27,28],"strong",{},"Note","\nThis was written in 2019. The oh-my-posh setup commands here are for v2. oh-my-posh has since moved to v3+ which is cross-platform but uses different config commands. Check the oh-my-posh official docs for the current installation instructions if you're setting up fresh.",[12,31,33],{"id":32},"my-setup","My setup",[17,35,36],{},"For reference:",[38,39,40],"ul",{},[41,42,43],"li",{},"Windows 10, version 1903",[17,45,46],{},"One of the customizations below requires version 1903 specifically.",[17,48,49],{},"I also use PowerShell, so this post focuses on PowerShell customization.",[51,52,54],"h3",{"id":53},"checking-your-windows-version","Checking your Windows version",[17,56,57,58,62],{},"Type ",[59,60,61],"code",{},"winver"," in the search bar:",[17,64,65],{},[66,67],"img",{"alt":68,"src":69},"winver search","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FgFP7UBa.png",[17,71,72],{},[66,73],{"alt":74,"src":75},"Windows version","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F6C78BAf.png",[12,77,79],{"id":78},"adding-a-git-style-prompt","Adding a git-style prompt",[17,81,82],{},"Default PowerShell prompt looks like this:",[17,84,85],{},[66,86],{"alt":87,"src":88},"Plain PowerShell","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FxI70onO.png",[17,90,91],{},"We're going to upgrade it to this:",[17,93,94],{},[66,95],{"alt":96,"src":97},"Prettified prompt","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002Fmxj9VeZ.png",[17,99,100,101,104],{},"The prompt magic comes from ",[59,102,103],{},"oh-my-posh",". Setup below.",[17,106,107],{},[108,109,113],"a",{"href":110,"rel":111},"https:\u002F\u002Fgithub.com\u002FJanDeDobbeleer\u002Foh-my-posh",[112],"nofollow","oh-my-posh GitHub",[12,115,117],{"id":116},"installing-oh-my-posh","Installing oh-my-posh",[51,119,121],{"id":120},"prerequisite","Prerequisite",[17,123,124],{},"Open PowerShell and run:",[126,127,132],"pre",{"className":128,"code":129,"language":130,"meta":131,"style":131},"language-ps shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","Install-Module posh-git -Scope CurrentUser\n","ps","",[59,133,134],{"__ignoreMap":131},[135,136,139],"span",{"class":137,"line":138},"line",1,[135,140,129],{},[17,142,143,144,147],{},"First time installing modules, NuGet will ask a bunch of questions — just ",[59,145,146],{},"Y"," through them. (I'm not screenshotting since I'm already past this.)",[51,149,151],{"id":150},"install-oh-my-posh","Install oh-my-posh",[126,153,155],{"className":128,"code":154,"language":130,"meta":131,"style":131},"Install-Module oh-my-posh -Scope CurrentUser\n",[59,156,157],{"__ignoreMap":131},[135,158,159],{"class":137,"line":138},[135,160,154],{},[17,162,163,164,166],{},"Same — ",[59,165,146],{}," through prompts.",[51,168,170],{"id":169},"set-it-to-auto-apply","Set it to auto-apply",[17,172,57,173,176],{},[59,174,175],{},"$profile"," in PowerShell to see your PowerShell profile path:",[17,178,179],{},[66,180],{"alt":181,"src":182},"profile path","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F8Plz4sS.png",[17,184,185],{},"Open the folder:",[126,187,191],{"className":188,"code":189,"language":190,"meta":131,"style":131},"language-cmd shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","C:\\Users\\Hsiangfeng\\Documents\\WindowsPowerShell\\\n","cmd",[59,192,193],{"__ignoreMap":131},[135,194,195],{"class":137,"line":138},[135,196,189],{},[17,198,199,200,203],{},"If there's no ",[59,201,202],{},"Microsoft.PowerShell_profile.ps1",", create one. Add this:",[126,205,207],{"className":128,"code":206,"language":130,"meta":131,"style":131},"Import-Module posh-git\nImport-Module oh-my-posh\nSet-Theme Agnoster\n",[59,208,209,214,220],{"__ignoreMap":131},[135,210,211],{"class":137,"line":138},[135,212,213],{},"Import-Module posh-git\n",[135,215,217],{"class":137,"line":216},2,[135,218,219],{},"Import-Module oh-my-posh\n",[135,221,223],{"class":137,"line":222},3,[135,224,225],{},"Set-Theme Agnoster\n",[17,227,228],{},"Now every time PowerShell starts, the prompt is themed automatically.",[17,230,231,232,235,236,241],{},"For different themes, change ",[59,233,234],{},"Set-Theme",". The official GitHub README has the ",[108,237,240],{"href":238,"rel":239},"https:\u002F\u002Fgithub.com\u002FJanDeDobbeleer\u002Foh-my-posh#themes",[112],"oh-my-posh themes list",".",[12,243,245],{"id":244},"windows-terminal","Windows Terminal",[17,247,248],{},"Now my favorite part — Windows Terminal. Microsoft released this in 2019 as a modern replacement for the old console host:",[17,250,251],{},[66,252],{"alt":245,"src":253},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F9DttRqa.png",[17,255,256],{},"Before going further, confirm:",[38,258,259,262,265],{},[41,260,261],{},"You're on Windows 10",[41,263,264],{},"Version 1903 or higher",[41,266,267],{},"(Optional) Combined with the oh-my-posh setup above",[17,269,270],{},"If you're set, let's install.",[51,272,274],{"id":273},"install-windows-terminal","Install Windows Terminal",[17,276,277,278,282],{},"Install via the Microsoft Store — click ",[108,279,281],{"href":280},"ms-windows-store:\u002F\u002Fpdp\u002F?ProductId=9n0dx20hk701","this link"," to open the Store directly.",[17,284,285],{},[66,286],{"alt":287,"src":288},"Already installed","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FeeRMQpT.png",[17,290,291],{},"After install, search \"Windows Terminal\" — I'd recommend pinning it to the start menu:",[17,293,294],{},[66,295],{"alt":296,"src":297},"Windows Terminal in start menu","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FFeQuH7s.png",[12,299,301],{"id":300},"customizing-windows-terminal","Customizing Windows Terminal",[17,303,304],{},"On launch it'll look similar to plain PowerShell. Click the down arrow next to the tabs → Settings:",[17,306,307],{},[66,308],{"alt":309,"src":310},"Settings","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FRr5CMTx.png",[17,312,313,314,317],{},"Search ",[59,315,316],{},"profiles"," — you'll see three objects, each representing a shell:",[17,319,320],{},[66,321],{"alt":316,"src":322},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FNOKHU7p.png",[17,324,325],{},"The order matches the dropdown order. For PowerShell, edit the first one:",[17,327,328],{},[66,329],{"alt":330,"src":331},"profiles detail","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002Fok0af8l.png",[17,333,334],{},"Annotated example of what I edited:",[17,336,337],{},[66,338],{"alt":339,"src":340},"Annotated profile config","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FGSpwjDv.png",[17,342,343],{},"Two important things:",[38,345,346,352],{},[41,347,348,351],{},[26,349,350],{},"Background image path can't contain non-ASCII characters"," — otherwise the image won't load.",[41,353,354,357,358,361],{},[26,355,356],{},"Pick a proper font."," I use ",[59,359,360],{},"Sarasa Term SC",". Without a nerd font \u002F powerline-aware font, oh-my-posh's special characters render incorrectly.",[17,363,364],{},"End result:",[17,366,367],{},[66,368],{"alt":369,"src":370},"Result","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FLhk3iVp.png",[372,373,374],"style",{},"html .default .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}",{"title":131,"searchDepth":216,"depth":216,"links":376},[377,378,381,382,387,390],{"id":14,"depth":216,"text":15},{"id":32,"depth":216,"text":33,"children":379},[380],{"id":53,"depth":222,"text":54},{"id":78,"depth":216,"text":79},{"id":116,"depth":216,"text":117,"children":383},[384,385,386],{"id":120,"depth":222,"text":121},{"id":150,"depth":222,"text":151},{"id":169,"depth":222,"text":170},{"id":244,"depth":216,"text":245,"children":388},[389],{"id":273,"depth":222,"text":274},{"id":300,"depth":216,"text":301},"Misc","2019-09-24 13:53:52","Staring at the same plain PowerShell prompt all day gets old. This post walks through giving Windows PowerShell a git-style prompt with oh-my-posh, plus installing and customizing Windows Terminal (the newer Microsoft terminal) — themes, fonts, background image. Heads up — this article was written in 2019; oh-my-posh has since moved to v3+ which uses different config commands.","md","en",{},true,"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002Fcustomize-windows-terminal-with-oh-my-posh","2",{"title":6,"description":393},false,"en\u002FMisc\u002Fcustomize-windows-terminal-with-oh-my-posh",[404,405],"Software","Terminal",null,"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2019\u002F09\u002F24\u002Fcustomize-windows-terminal-with-oh-my-posh\u002F","Y5YaKIQW-se0r1T1sW2XJXbBtSGxyAt2yOzZPoXA4w8",{"newer":410,"older":414},{"url":411,"title":412,"date":413},"\u002Fen\u002Fphp\u002F2019\u002F09\u002F25\u002Fphp-thinkphp-day-24-form-validation-02\u002F","Day 24 - Learning ThinkPHP from Scratch: Form Validation (2)","2019-09-25 00:00:05",{"url":415,"title":416,"date":417},"\u002Fen\u002Fphp\u002F2019\u002F09\u002F24\u002Fthink-php-day-23-form-validation-01\u002F","ThinkPHP Day 23: Form Validation, Part 1","2019-09-24 00:00:26",[419,424,429],{"url":420,"title":421,"date":422,"readingMinutes":423},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F06\u002F23\u002Fmac-stats-menu-bar-system-monitor\u002F","Stats — The Free Open-Source macOS Menu Bar System Monitor I Use Every Day (CPU, GPU, Temperature, Network)","2026-06-23 10:00:00","5",{"url":425,"title":426,"date":427,"readingMinutes":428},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F05\u002F26\u002Fhow-much-does-a-blog-really-earn-with-google-adsense\u002F","Can a Blog Really Make Tens of Thousands of Dollars a Month? Real Google AdSense Numbers, Explained","2026-05-26 21:00:00","6",{"url":430,"title":431,"date":432,"readingMinutes":433},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F05\u002F18\u002Fvscode-disable-integrated-browser-auto-open\u002F","VSCode Opens Every Link in the Integrated Browser? How to Disable Auto Takeover","2026-05-18 14:30:00","4",1784013065545]